commenter.bio: S

message.body: @terpgg Valid inputs are A, B, Z, L, R, Start, CUp, CDown, CLeft, CRight (C buttons), DUp, DDown, DLeft, DRight (D-Pad, unused in most games), Up, Down, Left and Right (Analog stick, used in almost every game as the standard movement input). Typos

fragments.text: @terpgg Valid inputs are A, B, Z, L, R, Start, CUp, CDown, CLeft, CRight (C buttons), DUp, DDown, DLeft, DRight (D-Pad, unused in most games), Up, Down, Left and Right (Analog stick, used in almost every game as the standard movement input). Typos

message.body: work too! Directions can be replaced with cardinal directions: N, S, W, E, North, South, West, East, this works for C buttons and D-Pad too. ex: CN, CNorth, DS, DSouth, etc. Up to 3 DIFFERENT commands can be used AT THE SAME TIME, NOT ONE AFTER

fragments.text: work too! Directions can be replaced with cardinal directions: N, S, W, E, North, South, West, East, this works for C buttons and D-Pad too. ex: CN, CNorth, DS, DSouth, etc. Up to 3 DIFFERENT commands can be used AT THE SAME TIME, NOT ONE AFTER

message.body: ANOTHER: b+up+right. You can't use opposite commands at the same time: Left+Right, Up+Down, etc., WILL NOT WORK. End your input with - to hold down indefinitely until the next input comes: a+z+right-. Alternatively, you can type Wait or Stop to stop

fragments.text: ANOTHER: b+up+right. You can't use opposite commands at the same time: Left+Right, Up+Down, etc., WILL NOT WORK. End your input with - to hold down indefinitely until the next input comes: a+z+right-. Alternatively, you can type Wait or Stop to stop
